    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you on the heritage aspect, but the market is changing. We have massive wealth growth in places like East Asia, the Middle East, and among Black entrepreneurs in the US and Africa. If our creative direction is strictly tied to \"European aristocracy,\" aren't we basically saying that people from those other backgrounds don't fit the \"ideal\" luxury lifestyle or aren't the right kind of consumers for a brand like this? How would you justify that to a stakeholder who wants to capture those growing markets?",
